'''Zina Mahjoub''' 'الثعبان' (literally translated to ''The Snake'') (October 5, 1933 – May 28, 1957) was a [[Sudan]]ese [[poet]] and songwriter during the early 20th century. She also became the celebrated poet [[Rashad Hashim]]'s mistress and long-time muse, inspiring his famous poem ''The One Who Makes The Sun Shine''.
Mahjoub died on May 28, 1957 while giving birth to her third child.
